84,84,,,"[('', '')]","Nữ danh ca đã có những chia sẻ thẳng thắn khi phải đối mặt với những câu hỏi xoay quanh bê bối của chồng.

Vừa qua, Mỹ Tâm đã có dịp diện kiến truyền hình để chia sẻ những điều chưa từng tiết lộ về cuộc sống, sự nghiệp và cả những định hướng tương lai của mình. Bên cạnh đó, cô cũng có những chia sẻ thẳng thắn khi phải đối mặt với những câu hỏi xoay quanh bê bối của chồng mình.

Cụ thể, trong cuộc trò chuyện cùng MC, khi được hỏi về cảm xúc của mình suốt thời gian qua khi phải đối mặt với những ồn ào từ phía chồng, Mỹ Tâm đã có phần lúng túng nhưng sau đó cô vẫn bình tĩnh trả lời: ""Thật ra thì Tâm cũng không có gì để nói về chuyện này, bởi vì Tâm không biết gì về cách quản lý của chồng mình"".

Nữ ca sĩ tiếp tục chia sẻ: ""Tâm chỉ biết rằng Tâm làm một ca sĩ, Tâm chịu trách nhiệm với âm nhạc của mình, khán giả yêu thương mình thế nào, họ sẽ nhìn mình làm như thế nào. Chứ Tâm không bao giờ để những chuyện ồn ào của người khác làm ảnh hưởng đến con đường của mình"".

Mỹ Tâm cũng thừa nhận rằng, suốt thời gian qua, cô vẫn đọc được những bài báo đăng tải về vụ việc của chồng. Tuy nhiên, nữ ca sĩ cho rằng việc mình trả lời phỏng vấn về vấn đề này cũng chẳng giải quyết được gì nên cô quyết định im lặng.
Nếu Tâm là khán giả, Tâm sẽ bình thường lắm. Tâm sẽ bảo rằng 'Ồ, chồng cô Mỹ Tâm vậy à? Thôi, chuyện người ta, kệ người ta'. Tâm cũng chẳng quan tâm lắm"", nữ ca sĩ chia sẻ.

Trước đó, vào tháng 10 năm 2022, chồng của Mỹ Tâm đã vướng phải một vụ lùm xùm liên quan đến quản lý tiền bạc của công ty. Ông đã bị các cộng sự của mình tố cáo về việc không minh bạch trong việc chi trả tiền lương và tiền thưởng, đồng thời còn có hành vi cố tình quỵt nợ. Vụ việc đã khiến dư luận xôn xao trong một thời gian dài và gây ảnh hưởng không nhỏ đến hình ảnh của Mỹ Tâm.

Tuy nhiên, bất chấp những ồn ào từ phía chồng, Mỹ Tâm vẫn giữ thái độ im lặng và tập trung vào sự nghiệp ca hát của mình. Cô vẫn chăm chỉ đi diễn, ra mắt các sản phẩm âm nhạc mới và nhận được sự ủng hộ nhiệt tình từ khán giả.",0

What is the biggest limit to renewable energy?

The biggest limit to renewable energy is intermittency. Solar and wind power are not always available, so they cannot be relied upon to provide a constant supply of electricity. This means that we need to find ways to store energy from these sources when they are available so that we can use it when they are not.

There are a number of ways to store energy, but they are all expensive and inefficient. This makes renewable energy more expensive than fossil fuels. However, the costs of renewable energy are falling, and as they continue to fall, renewable energy will become more competitive with fossil fuels.

Another limit to renewable energy is the fact that it is not always available in the places where it is needed. For example, solar power is not available at night, and wind power is not available when the wind is not blowing. This means that we need to find ways to transmit energy from areas where it is abundant to areas where it is needed.
The long-distance transmission of electricity is expensive and inefficient. This makes it difficult to take advantage of renewable energy sources that are located in remote areas.

Despite these challenges, renewable energy is becoming increasingly important in the fight against climate change. As the costs of renewable energy continue to fall, and as we develop new ways to store and transmit energy, renewable energy will become a more and more important part of our energy mix.

87,87,,,"[('', '')]","Mahasiswa S-1 Fakultas Geografi Universitas Muhammadiyah Surakarta (UMS) yang tergabung dalam kelompok Kuliah Kerja Nyata-Tematik (KKN-T) melakukan sosialisasi tentang pentingnya pengelolaan sampah berbasis masyarakat. Kegiatan yang berlangsung pada Minggu (6/2/2022) ini dilaksanakan di dua kelurahan, yaitu Kelurahan Mangkubumen dan Kelurahan Pasar Kliwon, Kecamatan Banjarsari, Kota Surakarta.

Sosialisasi ini merupakan bagian dari program kerja KKN-T yang bertemakan ""Peningkatan Kesadaran Masyarakat dalam Pengelolaan Sampah Berbasis Masyarakat"". Program ini bertujuan untuk meningkatkan kesadaran masyarakat tentang pentingnya pengelolaan sampah yang baik dan benar, serta mendorong masyarakat untuk berperan aktif dalam pengelolaan sampah di lingkungannya.

Kegiatan sosialisasi ini diawali dengan memberikan edukasi kepada masyarakat tentang berbagai permasalahan lingkungan yang disebabkan oleh sampah, seperti pencemaran udara, pencemaran air, dan kerusakan ekosistem. Selanjutnya, masyarakat diberikan pemahaman tentang pentingnya pengelolaan sampah yang baik dan benar, serta berbagai cara untuk mengelola sampah dengan baik.

Setelah sosialisasi, mahasiswa KKN-T bersama dengan masyarakat melakukan kerja bakti membersihkan lingkungan dari sampah. Kegiatan ini bertujuan untuk menumbuhkan rasa peduli masyarakat terhadap kebersihan lingkungan dan mendorong masyarakat untuk membuang sampah pada tempatnya.

Ketua kelompok KKN-T, Rizki Anggraini, berharap kegiatan sosialisasi dan kerja bakti ini dapat meningkatkan kesadaran masyarakat tentang pentingnya pengelolaan sampah yang baik dan benar. Ia juga berharap masyarakat dapat berperan aktif dalam pengelolaan sampah di lingkungannya sehingga dapat terwujud lingkungan yang bersih dan sehat.

Kami berharap dengan adanya kegiatan sosialisasi dan kerja bakti ini, kesadaran masyarakat tentang pentingnya pengelolaan sampah dapat meningkat. Selain itu, kami juga berharap masyarakat dapat berperan aktif dalam pengelolaan sampah di lingkungannya sehingga dapat terwujud lingkungan yang bersih dan sehat,"" ujar Rizki.

Salah satu warga Kelurahan Mangkubumen, Suwarti, mengapresiasi kegiatan sosialisasi dan kerja bakti yang dilakukan oleh mahasiswa KKN-T UMS. Ia mengatakan bahwa kegiatan ini sangat bermanfaat bagi masyarakat karena dapat menambah pengetahuan tentang pengelolaan sampah dan mendorong masyarakat untuk membuang sampah pada tempatnya.

Kegiatan ini sangat bermanfaat bagi kami, karena kami dapat menambah pengetahuan tentang pengelolaan sampah dan juga terdorong untuk membuang sampah pada tempatnya. Kami berharap kegiatan seperti ini dapat terus dilakukan secara berkala sehingga masyarakat dapat semakin sadar tentang pentingnya pengelolaan sampah yang baik dan benar,"" kata Suwarti.",0

Find the term in the linear of the form $an+b$ that contains $10949$
Find the term in the linear of the form $an+b$ that contains $10949$
Given that the linear equation is $11n+10$, we need to determine the value of $n$ that makes this equation equal to $10949$.
Therefore, the term in the linear equation that contains $10949$ is $11(995)+10=\boxed{10949}$",0
93,93,,,"[('', '')]","Я обоствую все рецепты, приготовленные в горшочках, особенно мясные. Попробуйте и вы!
1. Мясо нарезать на крупные куски, обжарить на сковороде до румяной корочки.
2. Картофель, морковь и лук очистить, нарезать крупными кубиками.
3. В горшочки для запекания выложить слоями: мясо, картофель, морковь, лук.
4. Посолить, поперчить, добавить измельченный чеснок и зелень.
5. Влить в каждый горшочек воду или бульон.
6. Накрыть горшочки крышками и поставить в разогретую духовку до 180°С на 40-50 минут.
7. Готовое жаркое подавать к столу в горшочках, посыпав свежей зеленью.",0

98,98,,,"[('', '')]","So, you’re graduating soon and you’re not sure what you want to do with your life. You’re not alone. Many people feel the same way. The good news is that there are a lot of things you can do to figure out your future. Here are a few suggestions:

1. **Talk to Your Friends and Family:** Your friends and family know you best, so they can offer valuable insights into your strengths and weaknesses. They may also have suggestions for career paths that you might not have considered.

2. **Take Some Career Assessments:** There are a number of career assessments available online and through career counseling services. These assessments can help you identify your interests, skills, and values.

3. **Explore Different Career Paths:** Once you have a better understanding of your interests and skills, you can start exploring different career paths. Talk to people who work in different fields, read articles and books about different careers, and attend career fairs.

4. **Get Some Experience:** One of the best ways to figure out if a career is right for you is to get some experience in the field. This could involve volunteering, interning, or shadowing someone who works in the field.
5. **Don’t Be Afraid to Change Your Mind:** It’s okay to change your mind about your career goals. You may find that your interests and skills change over time.

Remember, there is no one-size-fits-all approach to figuring out your future. The most important thing is to take the time to explore your options and find a career path that you’re passionate about.",0

In the ongoing $14 \mathrm{TeV} \mathrm{LHC}$ run, the LHCb experiment will collect an integrated luminosity of $9 \mathrm{fb}^{-1}$, corresponding to 5 times the present dataset. To exploit this large dataset, a significant upgrade of the present LHCb detector is planned to be installed during the 2019/2020 Long Shutdown 2. This upgrade mainly concerns the tracking system and the trigger strategy. The upgraded LHCb detector will continue to perform searches for physics beyond the Standard Model with increased sensitivity, but will also open new possibilities in $B$-physics and charm physics measurements. In this paper, the planned upgrade of the LHCb detector and the physics prospects of the upgraded LHCb detector in the area of rare decays, charm physics and searches for New Physics are summarized.

The LHCb experiment at the Large Hadron Collider (LHC) has collected data at a centre-of-mass energy of $7 \mathrm{TeV}$ in 2010 , at $8 \mathrm{TeV}$ in 2011 and at 13 TeV in 2015 and 2016. The total luminosity collected so far corresponds to $3 \mathrm{fb}^{-1}$ of integrated luminosity. The excellent performance of the LHCb detector allowed the collaboration to significantly contribute to the measurements of the Cabibbo-Kobayashi-Maskawa matrix elements, as well as to the physics of heavy hadrons, for which LHCb provides a unique, clean environment. The flavour sector is also one of the key areas for the LHCb experiment for the search for new physics processes, which are predicted by theories beyond the Standard Model (SM). These theories are motivated by the lack of understanding of some fundamental problems in particle physics, such as the origin of mass, the existence of dark matter and dark energy, and the matterantimatter asymmetry of universe.

The LHCb experiment has so far analysed about $1 \mathrm{fb}^{-1}$ of data, and has already reported a number of interesting results. In particular, the search for $B_{s}^{0} \rightarrow \mu^{+} \mu^{-}$is arguably one of the most impressive results obtained in 2012 [1], with the first observation of this decay, and the measurement of its branching ratio and time evolution. Much attention was also devoted to the time-dependent $C P$ asymmetry of $B^{0} \rightarrow \pi^{+} \pi^{-}$and $B^{0} \rightarrow K^{+} \pi^{-}$decays, induced by $B_{d}^{0}-\bar{B}_{d}^{0}$ mixing, in which significant deviations from the SM predictions were observed [2].

Furthermore, in 2015 and 2016, the LHCb experiment has observed a number of new charm meson resonances $[3,4]$. In particular, the LHCb collaboration has reported the first observation of the doubly charmed meson $\Xi_{c c}^{++}$, and of the $\Xi_{c c}^{0}$ resonance, as well as the first evidence for the existence of the hidden-charm pentaquark $P_{c}(4312)^{+}$.

${ }^{*}$ Speaker, \href{mailto:maurizio.martini@rhul.ac.uk}{maurizio.martini@rhul.ac.uk} The LHCb detector has also explored various channels in which New Physics could manifest itself. In particular, LHCb has searched for lepton flavour violation decays such as $B_{s}^{0} \rightarrow \mu^{\pm} e^{\mp}, B^{+} \rightarrow$ $K^{+} \mu^{\pm} e^{\mp}$ and $B^{0} \rightarrow K^{0} \mu^{\pm} e^{\mp}$ [5], for $B_{(s)}^{0} \rightarrow \tau^{+} \tau^{-}$decays [6], for dark photon final states, in the $\mu^{+} \mu^{-}$[7] and $\pi^{0} \gamma$ [8] channels, for invisible decays such as $B^{+} \rightarrow K^{*+}$ invis and $B_{s}^{0} \rightarrow \phi \gamma$ [9], and for long-lived particles, in the $B_{c}^{+} \rightarrow J / \psi \pi^{\pm} X$ [10] and $B_{s}^{0} \rightarrow \mu^{+} \mu^{-} X$ [11] channels. In all cases, no significant excess over the background expectations has been observed.

The LHCb experiment is scheduled to continue data taking until the end of 2018, with a total integrated luminosity of about $6 \mathrm{fb}^{-1}$ of data, corresponding to 6 times the present dataset. A significant upgrade of the experiment is planned to be installed during the Long Shutdown 2 (LS2) in 2019/2020, in order to fully exploit the high luminosity of the LHC in Run 3 and beyond. The goal of the upgrade is to collect and analyse a total of $50 \mathrm{fb}^{-1}$ of data during Run 3 and Run 4. In order to achieve this goal, the LHCb experiment will operate at a luminosity of $2 \times 10^{33} \mathrm{~cm}^{-2} \mathrm{~s}^{-1}$, and with a pile-up of 40 interactions per bunch crossing.

The LHCb upgrade mainly concerns the tracking system and the trigger strategy. The present inner tracker, which is made of silicon micro-strip detectors, will be replaced by a new tracker, the so-called Upstream Tracker (UT), made of scintillating fibre (SciFi) trackers. The UT will extend the coverage of the detector to a pseudo-rapidity region $\eta<2.5$, and will provide a better impact parameter and momentum resolution in the forward region $(2<\eta<5)$, where the tracking efficiency for the present tracker is less than $50 \%$. A new Outer Tracker (OT) will be introduced, which will increase the ghost rate, a major source of background in the LHCb experiment. To deal with the increase of the ghost track rate, the present silicon-strip detectors will be upgraded with the use of either new micro-strip modules or single-sided large area sensors, depending on the final cost estimate. The present silicon-strip detectors will also be upgraded with a new cooling system. The present beam-pipe, which contributes to the multiple-scattering budget, will be replaced with a beryllium pipe.

The upgrade of the detector will also involve the installation of two additional ring-imaging Cherenkov (RICH) detectors, which will be placed upstream from the magnet. A new trigger scheme will be developed, which will take advantage of the information from the RICH detectors, to further reduce the trigger rate and to improve the performance of the trigger algorithms.

The upgrade of the LHCb detector is expected to extend the physics reach of the experiment, such as by improving the measurements of the $C P$ violation in $B$ and $D$ decays, by searching for lepton flavour violation, by exploring the physics of heavy flavour baryons, and by searching for New Physics.

The main goal of the LHCb upgrade is to explore the flavour sector of the SM with higher precision, and to search for rare decays which may be a sign of the presence of new physics. In this section, the physics prospects of the LHCb upgrade are summarized. The results for some representative decay channels are shown in Table 1 , where the expected statistical uncertainty on the branching ratios for the different decay channels is shown, as well as the SM predictions. The systematic uncertainties, which were not considered in the calculation of the expected statistical uncertainties, will be evaluated with the full Run 3 dataset.

The branching ratio of the $B_{(s)}^{0} \rightarrow \mu^{+} \mu^{-}$decays is predicted by the SM to be $3.66(17) \times 10^{-9}$ for $B_{s}^{0}[12],(1.06 \pm 0.09) \times 10^{-6}$ for $B^{0}[13]$ and $(1.03 \pm 0.12) \times 10^{-6}$ for $B^{+}$[13]. The uncertainty on the $B_{s}^{0} \rightarrow \mu^{+} \mu^{-}$branching ratio is dominated by the uncertainty on the $V_{t d}$ matrix element. The preliminary LHCb measurement of the $B_{s}^{0} \rightarrow \mu^{+} \mu^{-}$branching ratio is $(3.0 \pm 0.6 \pm 0.3) \times 10^{-9}$ [1]. With the LHCb upgrade, the precision of the measurement will be improved by a factor of 4 , allowing a test of the SM at the level of $2 \sigma$.

The $B_{s}^{0} \rightarrow e^{+} e^{-}$and $B^{0} \rightarrow e^{+} e^{-}$branching ratios are predicted by the SM to be $11.7(4.0) \times 10^{-14}$ and $8.2(3.2) \times 10^{-15}$, respectively [12]. The LHCb upgrade will allow to search for these decays in final states with a single reconstructed electron, with a $5 \sigma$ discovery potential for both decay modes. A similar result is expected for the $B^{+} \rightarrow e^{+} e^{-}$decays, with a $2.",0

100,100,,,"[('', '')]","It happens to all of us. There are days when we just can’t focus. We’re easily distracted, our minds are racing, and we can’t seem to get anything done. When this happens, it can be helpful to take a break and do something that will help you clear your head and refocus.
Here are a few tips for refocusing when you’re feeling distracted:
* **Take a walk**: Get some fresh air and exercise. This will help to clear your head and give you a new perspective.
* **Meditate**: Meditating for even a few minutes can help to calm your mind and focus your attention.
* **Listen to music**: Listening to music can help to block out distractions and put you in a more focused state of mind.
* **Take a nap**: Sometimes, the best way to refocus is to take a nap. When you wake up, you’ll be feeling refreshed and ready to start again.
* **Change your environment**: If you’re feeling distracted by your surroundings, try changing your environment. Go to a different room, or even go outside for a while.
* **Set priorities**: Make a list of the things that you need to do, and then prioritize them. This will help you to focus on the most important tasks first.
* **Break down tasks**: If a task seems too daunting, break it down into smaller, more manageable steps. This will make it seem less overwhelming and easier to focus on.
* **Reward yourself**: When you complete a task, reward yourself. This will help you to stay motivated and focused.
If you’re struggling to refocus, don’t be afraid to ask for help. Talk to a friend, family member, or therapist. They can provide you with support and guidance.",0

Ölüm, hastalık, üzüntü veya başka bir nedenden dolayı huzurunuz kaçmış, çok sıkıntı çekiyor, çok üzülüyor ve bunalıma girmişseniz bu yazımızı dikkatle okumanızı canı gönülden tavsiye ederiz. Bu yazımızı okuduğunuzda mutlaka teselli bulacaksınız ve moraliniz düzelecektir.

Her ne kadar bu dünyada çok sıkıntı ve ıstırap görsek de, yeryüzü, hâlâ iyilerin ve güzelliklerin de olduğu bir yerdir. Size burada bazı güzel şeylerden bahsedeceğiz. Ama siz hayal gücünüzü kullanarak bunların daha iyilerini de bulabilirsiniz.
İşte size dünyayı daha güzel gösteren bazı gerçekler:
Etrafınıza iyi bakındığınızda bu gerçekleri siz de göreceksiniz. Bu gerçekler sizi rahatlatacak ve moralinizi düzeltecektir.

Yaşamın şartları ne kadar zor olursa olsun, yine de mutlaka sevinilecek bir şey bulabilirsiniz. Mesela, sağlıklı olmak, sevilen insanlara sahip olmak, bir işe sahip olmak, hayatta olmanın kendisi bile sevilmeye değer şeylerdir. Hayatın güzel yönlerine odaklanın ve hayatın tadını çıkarmaya çalışın.

Elbette ki, hayat her zaman kolay değildir. Hepimiz zorluklar ve sıkıntılarla karşılaşırız. Ama bu zorlukları aşmak için elimizden geleni yapmalıyız. Zorlukları aşmak için mücadele etmek, bizi daha güçlü ve daha dirençli hale getirir.
Hayatta karşılaştığınız zorluklar karşısında asla vazgeçmeyin. Hep umutlu olun ve mücadele etmeye devam edin. Günün birinde mutlaka başaracaksınız.
Hayatla ilgili bazı gerçekler vardır ki, bunlar sizi daha iyi hissettirecektir. Bunları aklınızda tutun ve asla unutmayın.
Bu gerçekleri kabul ettiğinizde, hayatla daha kolay başa çıkabilirsiniz. Hayata dair beklentilerinizi gerçekçi hale getirdiğinizde, daha az hayal kırıklığı yaşarsınız.
Hayatın zorlukları karşısında umudunuzu kaybetmeyin. Her zaman daha iyi günlerin geleceğini unutmayın. Zorluklar sizi daha güçlü hale getirecektir. Vazgeçmeyin ve mücadele etmeye devam edin.",0

105,105,,,"[('', '')]","

Bībele ir vispopulārākā grāmata pasaulē, taču ļoti maz cilvēku to ir lasījuši

Bībele ir visvairāk tulkotajā un pārdotā grāmata pasaulē, tomēr ir ļoti maz cilvēku, kas to ir lasījuši. Aptauja, kas veica starp 1000 amerikāņiem, atklāja, ka tikai 22% respondentu ir izlasījuši visu Bībeli. Procentuālais daudzums cilvēku, kuri ir izlasījuši lielāko daļu Bībeles, ir vēl mazāks. Tikai 12% respondentu ir sacījuši, ka ir izlasījuši lielāko daļu Bībeles, bet 36% aptaujāto ir atzinuši, ka nav izlasījuši nevienu Bībeles grāmatu.

Ir vairāki iemesli, kāpēc tik maz cilvēku ir lasījuši visu Bībeli. Viens no iemesliem ir tas, ka Bībele ir ļoti gara grāmata. Tajā ir 66 grāmatas, kas varētu aizņemt vairākas nedēļas vai mēnešus. Cits iemesls ir tas, ka Bībele var būt grūti saprotama. Īpaši grūti ir saprast Vecajā Derībā aprakstītos notikumus.

Tomēr ir arī vairāki iemesli, kāpēc ir vērts izlasīt Bībeli. Pirmkārt, Bībele ir Dieva vārds. Tā ir grāmata, kas satur Dieva atklāsmi par pasauli un par cilvēka dzīvi. Bībele ir arī vēstures grāmata, kas stāsta par Dieva tautas vēsturi un par Dieva darbiem viņu labā. Treškārt, Bībele ir arī mācību grāmata, kas satur Dieva bauslības un kas māca cilvēkiem, kā dzīvot. Ceturtkārt, Bībele ir pravietojumu grāmata, kas satur Dieva pravietojumus par nākotni.
Bībele ir ļoti svarīga grāmata, kas ir vērts izlasīt ikvienam cilvēkam. Tā ir grāmata, kas var mainīt cilvēka dzīvi.",0
109,109,,,"[('', '')]","I'm running Ubuntu 8.04, and I'm having trouble connecting to my school's wireless network. When I try to connect, I get the following error message:
**Error: Authentication failed. Check your password and try again.**

I know that my password is correct, because I can log in to the network from my Windows XP laptop. I also know that my Ubuntu laptop is working properly, because I can connect to other wireless networks without any problems.
I've tried a few things to fix the problem, but nothing has worked. I've tried:
I'm not sure what else to try. Can anyone help me?
* I'm using a Linksys WRT54G wireless router.
* My school's wireless network is encrypted using WPA2.
* I'm using the ""wpa_supplicant"" driver to connect to the network.
* I have tried connecting to the network with both the GNOME Network Manager and the wicd Network Manager.
I have tried the following additional things:
* Manually setting the DNS servers in the Network Manager
* Using the ""wpa_passphrase"" tool to generate a WPA2 passphrase
None of these things have worked.
I have tried the following additional things:
* Installing the latest firmware for my wireless router
* Resetting my wireless router to factory defaults
* Connecting to the network with a different wireless adapter
None of these things have worked.

I have finally figured out the problem. My school's wireless network is using a RADIUS server for authentication. I needed to install the ""freeradius-client"" package on my Ubuntu laptop in order to connect to the network.
Once I installed the ""freeradius-client"" package, I was able to connect to the network without any problems.",0

110,110,,,"[('', '')]",按語：陳美燾（1896一1947），字子寅，號雨農。山東省肥城人。1919年畢業於北京京師大學預科後，考入北京大學政治系。1921年轉入法律系，1924年畢業。曾任北京大學政治學講座教授，法學院院長，國立北京大學副校長。1947年1月10日因心臟病逝世。陳美燾為中西法律教育事業融合同一，促進法學研究、教育的現代化，作出了積極貢獻。他是第一個在北京大學開講羅馬法和美國法課程的教授，第一個在北京大學召開羅馬法課堂討論的教授。他還發表了《羅馬法》等多篇學術論文，並出版了《法學通論》等3部著作。1927年，陳美燾創辦了《北大法學年報》，並擔任總編輯。該年報是民初在北京出版的惟一一本法學刊物，對法學研究、教育的發展起到了一定的促進作用。,0

113,113,,,"[('', '')]","A 29-year-old man, Wilson Joseph, has been arrested by men of the Ogun State Police Command for allegedly stealing a Honda Accord car with number plates FKJ453GH at gunpoint.

The suspect was arrested following a distress call received by the Divisional Police Officer, Ogijo Division, at about 10:30 pm from a yet-to-be identified victim, who reported that he had been trailed by some armed men from Lagos State to Ogijo and at a point, the men forced him to stop and dragged him out of his car.

The victim further stated that the robbers forcefully took away his Honda Accord car and escaped heading towards Ijebu-Ode. The DPO, Ogijo Division, CSP Muhammed Baba, quickly mobilised his men and the entire division was combed while all the exit points were blocked.
The police spokesman in Ogun State, Abimbola Oyeyemi, confirmed the arrest on Friday.

He said, “Their efforts yielded a positive result when the car was sighted along Ijebu Ode road. The robbers, on sighting the policemen, abandoned the car and took to their heels. They were chased and one of them, Wilson Joseph, was arrested.

“On interrogation, the suspect confessed to being a member of the robbery gang that snatched the car from its owner at gunpoint. He also informed the police that he works with a car dealer, adding that his duty is to steal cars for his boss, who usually goes out to sell them after they are stolen.
“Recovered from him was a locally-made pistol and two live cartridges, while the car has been taken to the station.”

According to Oyeyemi, the state Commissioner of Police, Lanre Bankole, has ordered the immediate transfer of the suspect to the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department for further investigation.
He added that the Commissioner of Police also directed the suspects’ accomplices to be hunted for and brought to book.",0

<blockquote id=""1"" pid=""0"" uid=""1"">It's because players don't get injured. They just get ""fatigued"".

118,118,,,"[('', '')]","Neuroscience is the study of the structure, function, development, and plasticity of the nervous system. It is a multidisciplinary field that draws on a variety of methods, including anatomy, physiology, molecular biology, and psychology.

Neuroscience has made significant advances in recent years, and we now have a much better understanding of how the brain works. However, there is still much that we do not know, and neuroscience remains an active and exciting field of research.
Here are some of the key areas of neuroscience research:
* The structure of the brain: This includes the different regions of the brain and how they are connected to each other.
* The function of the brain: This includes how the brain processes information, how it controls movement and behavior, and how it produces consciousness.
* The development of the brain: This includes how the brain changes from birth to adulthood.
* The plasticity of the brain: This includes the brain's ability to change its structure and function in response to experience.
Neuroscience research has a wide range of applications, including:

* The development of new treatments for neurological and psychiatric disorders: Neuroscience research is helping to identify the causes of these disorders and develop new drugs and therapies to treat them.

* The understanding of human behavior: Neuroscience research is helping us understand why we think, feel, and act the way we do. This knowledge can be used to develop new educational and therapeutic techniques.
* The development of new technologies: Neuroscience research is helping us develop new technologies, such as brain-computer interfaces and neuroprosthetics, that can help people with disabilities.
Neuroscience is a rapidly growing and exciting field of research with the potential to make a major impact on our understanding of the brain and its role in health, disease, and behavior.",0
119,119,,,"[('', '')]","En este artículo te vamos a contar qué diferencias existen entre un Trastorno de la Conducta Alimenticia (TCA) y un Trastorno de la ingestión de alimentos (TIA).
Cuando hablamos de TCA nos referimos a aquellas patologías que provocan trastornos en el apetito y en la ingesta de alimentos. Dentro de este grupo se encuentran:
* La anorexia nerviosa: se produce cuando la persona tiene un miedo intenso a ganar peso y realiza conductas para evitarlo.
* La bulimia nerviosa: se caracteriza por atracones de comida seguidos de vómitos autoinducidos o conductas compensatorias como el uso de laxantes, diuréticos o ejercicio excesivo.
* El trastorno por atracón: se trata de la ingestión de grandes cantidades de alimentos en un corto período de tiempo, seguido de una sensación de pérdida de control.

* El trastorno evitativo/restrictivo de la ingestión de alimentos: se caracteriza por una restricción o evitación de la ingesta de alimentos que no está motivada por una preocupación por el peso o la forma del cuerpo.
En cambio, los TIA son trastornos que afectan a la ingestión de alimentos, pero que no están motivados por una preocupación por el peso o la forma del cuerpo. Dentro de este grupo se encuentran:
* El trastorno de pica: se trata de la ingestión persistente de sustancias no nutritivas y no alimentarias.
* El trastorno de rumiación: se caracteriza por la regurgitación repetida de alimentos a la boca después de que estos hayan sido tragados.
* El trastorno de ingestión de alimentos: se trata de la ingestión repetida de alimentos no nutritivos, pero que no están clasificados como sustancias no alimentarias.

En general, los TCA son más graves que los TIA, ya que pueden provocar problemas de salud graves, como la desnutrición, la anemia, la osteoporosis y la infertilidad. Además, los TCA tienen un mayor riesgo de suicidio que los TIA.

El tratamiento de los TCA y los TIA suele incluir psicoterapia, medicación y cambios en los hábitos alimenticios. El tratamiento específico dependerá de la gravedad del trastorno y de las necesidades individuales de la persona.",0

- A function with arguments is a function that takes input values, known as arguments, and processes or operates on them to produce a result or perform a specific task.
- These arguments are passed to the function when it is called.
// Define a function called `add()` that takes two arguments
// Inside the function, we can use the arguments to perform calculations and operations
// We return the result of the operation
// Call the `add()` function with two arguments
// Print the result of the function call
console.log(""The sum of 10 and 20 is:"", sum)
- The function `add()` is defined with two arguments, `num1` and `num2`.
- When the function is called with two arguments (10 and 20 in this case), these values are passed to the function as `num1` and `num2`, respectively.
- Inside the `add()` function, we add the values of `num1` and `num2` using the `+` operator and store the result in `result`.
- We return the `result` variable, which is the sum of the two arguments.
- We call the `add()` function with the arguments 10 and 20, store the result in the `sum` variable, and then log the result to the console.
This example demonstrates how functions can be defined to accept arguments, perform operations on those arguments, and return a result based on the arguments passed to them.",0

<start_of_image> in the United States. On June 17, 1963, he delivered his “I Have a Dream” speech on the steps of the Lincoln Memorial during the March on Washington for Jobs and Freedom. While the civil rights movement had its roots in theReconstruction Era, it reached its climax during the 1950s and 1960s, when African Americans fought for basic rights and an end to segregation and discrimination. In 1954, the U.S. Supreme Court ruled in Brown v. Board of Education of Topeka that racial segregation of children in public schools was unconstitutional. This decision sparked a wave of protests and demonstrations, and in 1955, Rosa Parks, an African American woman, famously refused to give up her seat on a bus to a white man in Montgomery, Alabama. This incident helped to spark the Montgomery Bus Boycott, which lasted for more than a year and led to the desegregation of buses in Montgomery. In 1963, Martin Luther King Jr. led a series of nonviolent protests in Birmingham, Alabama, which resulted in the desegregation of public places in the city. In 1964, Congress passed the Civil Rights Act, which outlawed discrimination based on race, color, religion, sex, or national origin. In 1965, Congress passed the Voting Rights Act, which made it illegal for states to impose discriminatory voting practices. These laws helped to end segregation and discrimination, and they laid the foundation for the civil rights movement’s success. Today, the civil rights movement is considered to be one of the most important social movements in American history. It helped to end segregation and discrimination, and it paved the way for greater equality for all Americans.",0

I've thought about going to law school, but I'm not sure if I want to be a lawyer. I've also thought about getting a job in public service, but I don't know what kind of job I would want.
I'm just feeling really stuck right now. I don't know what I want to do with my life and I'm worried that I'm going to end up in a job that I hate.

I've talked to my family and friends about this, but they don't really have any advice. They just tell me to keep looking and that I'll eventually find something that I like. But it's been months and I still haven't found anything.
I'm starting to feel really discouraged. I don't know what I'm going to do with my life and I'm starting to think that I'm never going to find a job that I love.

<blockquote id=""1"" pid=""0"" uid=""1"">I felt the same way when I graduated with a degree in English, and I ended up in a job that I hated. It took me a few years to figure out what I wanted to do, but I eventually found a career that I love.
Here are a few things that helped me:
* **Talk to people.** Talk to your friends, family, professors, and anyone else who might be able to give you advice. They may have suggestions for jobs that you haven't even thought of.

* **Do some research.** Learn about different career paths and see what interests you. There are a lot of resources available online and in libraries. You can also find job shadowing and internship opportunities that can help you get a taste of what different jobs are like.

* **Don't be afraid to try new things.** It's okay to change your mind about what you want to do with your life. Most people do. Just be open to new experiences and be willing to step outside your comfort zone.

* **Don't give up.** It takes time to find a job that you love. Don't get discouraged if you don't find your dream job right away. Just keep looking and keep trying new things. Eventually, you'll find something that's a good fit for you.

It would be devastating. Crops would fail, animals would die, and people would starve. The economy would collapse, and there would be widespread social unrest. Governments would be overthrown, and wars would break out. The world would be a very different place.

column1: Згідно з переписом 2010 року, у місті мешкало 138 осіб у 63 домогосподарствах у складі 33 родин. Густота населення становила 59 осіб/км². Було 67 помешкань (29/км²).
До двох чи більше рас належало 1,4 %. Частка іспаномовних становила 1,4 % від усіх жителів.

За віковим діапазоном населення розподілялося таким чином: 22,5 % — особи молодші 18 років, 63,0 % — особи у віці 18—64 років, 14,5 % — особи у віці 65 років та старші. Медіана віку мешканця становила 39,0 року. На 100 осіб жіночої статі у місті припадало 97,1 чоловіків

137,137,,,[('', '')]","You can subscribe to the Pro Insight podcast via Spotify, iTunes or most podcast platforms.

column1: A gun AFL Academy member who wasn’t drafted until pick 65, Jordan Lisle was a fine player for Gold Coast and St Kilda in a career comprising 81 games and 51 goals. Now an assistant coach at Brisbane working under Chris Fagan, the 28-year-old is emerging as one of the most respected emerging coaches in the game.

In this podcast, Lisle gives remarkable insights into the transition from player to coach and the lessons he learned. He talks about spending a year at Richmond and working under Damien Hardwick before returning to Brisbane as a development coach, his early interactions with Fagan, the alternative pathways into coaching, and the modern-day traits of an AFL coach.

Lisle also talks about the evolution of high performance in the AFL and how coaches are increasingly looking for flexibility and the ability to adapt. He offers insights into the type of footy he likes to see played and the methods and data that shape modern coaching, while also discussing his own footy journey, his remarkable ability to kick long goals and the reasons he was overlooked in the draft.",0

139,139,,,"[('', '')]","De Vlinderstichting heeft dit harige rupsenachtige insect geplaatst in Verborgen schatten, een overzicht van 200 ongewervelde dieren die minder bekend zijn bij het grote publiek. Een vlinder die moeilijk te vinden is en weinig wordt opgemerkt. Maar die toch op veel plekken in Nederland voorkomt en een belangrijke rol speelt in het ecosysteem, zoals elke vlinder.

In tegenstelling tot de meeste vlindersoorten eten de rupsen van de gehoornde sikkelmot niet van bloemen. Hun lievelingskost is het bladgroen van de bladeren van eikenbomen. Eiken zijn sinds jaar en dag overal rondom de Middellandse Zee te vinden en eigenlijk in heel Europa tot aan Zuid-Scandinavië, Groot-Brittannië en Ierland. In zuidoost Europa komt deze vlinder zelfs voor in Turkije, Georgië en Armenië. Een groot leefgebied dus. Maar toch een smeltend leefgebied: het gevolg van menselijke activiteiten zoals ontbossing, vervuiling en klimaatverandering.

Wanneer de rupsen klaar zijn om te verpoppen bedekken ze zich met een zachte cocon uit zijde. Met behulp van het meegesleepte mos en de droge plantendeeltjes lijken ze op een klein stukje schors waardoor ze goed gecamoufleerd zijn. En ze zijn moeilijk te vinden. Op een kaartje van Nederland kleuren de provincies Noord-Holland, Zuid-Holland en Zeeland lichtblauw, de rest van het land is wit. Dit betekent dat de gehoornde sikkelmot in deze provincies minder dan 5 keer is waargenomen. Er zijn 23 provincies wit, dat betekent dat daar deze vlinder nooit is waargenomen. Er zijn 10 provincies donkerblauw, daar is de gehoornde sikkelmot meer dan 5 keer waargenomen. Dat zijn Groningen, Friesland, Drenthe, Overijssel, Flevoland, Gelderland, Noord-Brabant, Limburg en Utrecht. In deze provincies lijkt de gehoornde sikkelmot dus nog wel te overleven, maar hoe lang nog?

145,145,,,"[('', '')]","Children have long been used as the primary medium in marketing campaigns. Their innocent and trusting faces have the ability to tug at the heartstrings of consumers, making them more likely to purchase a product or service. However, there are several ethical issues that must be considered when using children in marketing campaigns.

**One of the biggest concerns is the potential for exploitation.** Children are particularly vulnerable to being taken advantage of, and they may not be fully aware of the implications of their participation in a marketing campaign. For example, they may be unaware that the product being advertised is not safe for them or that they are being paid less than adult models.

**Another concern is the potential for children to be misled or pressured into participating in a marketing campaign.** Children may be told that they will be famous or that they will receive a lot of money if they appear in an ad. They may also be pressured by their parents or guardians to participate in a campaign, even if they do not want to. This can lead to children feeling overwhelmed or exploited.

Finally, there is the concern that children may be exposed to inappropriate or harmful content in marketing campaigns.** For example, they may see ads for products that are not age-appropriate or that promote unhealthy behaviors. They may also be exposed to violence, sexual content, or other harmful messages.

Given these concerns, it is important for marketers to take steps to ensure that children are treated ethically when they are used in marketing campaigns. This includes obtaining parental consent, compensating children fairly, and protecting them from being exploited or misled. Marketers should also be mindful of the content of their campaigns and avoid exposing children to inappropriate or harmful material.",0

146,146,,,"[('', '')]","Nu har GP Legenden släppt ett avsnitt om forne stjärnan Martin Laursen. I avsnittet berättar Laursen om när han som 18-åring åkte till Holland för att spela i ADO Den Haag, om när han nästan dog och om sin tid i Aston Villa.
Han berättar även om sina bästa minnen från landslaget.

– När vi blev EM-tvåa 1992 var jag fem år och förstod kanske inte så mycket vad som hände. 1998 när vi åkte ut mot Brasilien var jag 11 år och då förstod jag mer, det var väldigt stort. Jag hade stenkoll på alla spelare i landslaget, hade deras kort och allt möjligt.
– Det var också speciellt när vi vann mot England 2000. Det var en stor seger, England hade ett riktigt bra lag på den tiden.
Martin Laursen dömde ut sig själv till döden efter att han hade drabbats av hjärtsvikt. Han tackar sin fru för att hon räddade honom.

– Jag bestämde mig för att jag skulle dö. Jag hade bara ångest och tänkte att det var nog nu. Jag ville inte leva så här längre. Jag ville bara att det skulle vara över. Men min hustru var en riktig superhjälte. Jag var verkligen nära att dö.
– Jag tackar Gud för att jag har min fru. Hon räddade mitt liv och tog hand om mig i en svår tid. Det är jag verkligen tacksam för.
Han berättar även om sin succétid i Aston Villa.

– Det är en av världens största fotbollsklubbar. Mycket av legendstatus gick att nå tack vare våra prestationer i Champions League, vi var uppe i semifinal en gång. Det är något som väldigt sällan händer för en dansk spelare att vara med i en semifinal i Champions League. Det är svårt att förklara vad man känner när man är i en sån miljö. Jag har många fina minnen därifrån.",0

150,150,,,"[('', '')]","There have been two common themes from club players and supporters alike with regard to the Harris Conferencing National League 1.
The first is concern at the shortened nature of the campaign. The second is a fear that the two “big teams” – Esher and Rotherham – would run away with the title.
Esher might have launched the season with a 20-point win (complete with a bonus point), but Rotherham’s defeat to Cinderford means that there’s at least a glimmer of hope for their rivals.

Indeed, the Titans were among the sides to benefit from the new side-entry laws as they scored four tries in the final quarter (two of which came after the 80th minute) to claim a famous 43-37 victory.
Scrum-half Jonny Arr was handed the Man of the Match award, but he was quick to deflect the praise.
“It was a great team performance,” Arr said. “Everybody dug in and put in a shift. I don’t think anyone would have thought that we’d come here and win by six points.
“It’s been the same at Cinds for the last few years. They’re always a big, physical pack, but we knew that we could move the ball and if we got some opportunities, we could score.
“To score four tries in the last 10 minutes, and three to win the game, it was just outstanding. We’ve recruited well in the summer and things are starting to come together.
“We’ve still got a long way to go, but we’ll take confidence from this win and look to kick on again next week.”
Jack Stapley, who had an eventful league debut for Cinderford, is in agreement with Arr that the new laws played a big part in deciding the outcome.
“I thought the new rules definitely came into effect a lot more than I thought they would,” Stapley said. “That try in the 80th minute was all down to the new rules.

“There was a lot of opportunity to play and I think Rotherham were caught out by it a little bit. They’re a big, physical side and we played a lot of rugby so they struggled to contain us towards the end of the game.
“They were quite quick to work out that you get rewarded for going fast and playing the ball quickly.
“I actually thought the new rules benefited us more than they did Rotherham. I think we were a lot better at exploiting the space, playing off nine and playing off 10.
“I thought we did really well. We lost by six points but I think we showed a lot of character to come back and score two tries in the last four minutes.
“We were showing a lot of energy and I think Rotherham struggled to contain us. We created a lot of chances and there was a lot of space out there for us.”
Stapley and Arr will both be back in action on Saturday as Cinderford travel to play Chinnor before Rotherham host Blackheath at Clifton Lane.",0

My apartment has one outlet in the ceiling, and the light hangs on an adjustable cord, so there’s no way to fit it in the outlet. Do I need to install a new outlet? If so, I don’t have any experience with electrical work and would like to avoid doing that on my own if possible.
The apartment manager said there’s nothing they can do. Is there any other way I could hang the light?

column1: If you avoid drilling holes in the ceiling, you won’t have to deal with the apartment manager being upset and trying to charge you to patch the holes. Our comprehensive Pre-owned vehicle checklist covers dozens of crucial inspection points, ensuring that your ride is performing in peak condition.

<start_of_image> on't let a few minor issues hold you back from owning that pre-owned vehicle you've been eyeing. With a little know-how and some basic tools, you can easily tackle many common repairs and restorations yourself.

2. Gather the Necessary Tools and Materials: Once you know what needs to be repaired, you can gather the necessary tools and materials. Make sure you have the right tools for the job, and that you have the right parts or materials for the repair.

3. Prepare the Vehicle: Before you start working on the vehicle, it's important to prepare it. This may involve removing any components that need to be accessed, such as wheels, tires, or panels. You may also need to disconnect the battery or drain the fluids.

4. Follow the Service Manual: When it comes to repairs and restorations, it's essential to follow the service manual. This will provide you with step-by-step instructions and ensure that you're performing the repair correctly.
5. Take Your Time: Don't rush through the repair or restoration process. Taking your time will ensure that you're doing the job right and that you're not causing any additional damage.
6. Be Careful: Always be careful when working on a vehicle. This means wearing the appropriate safety gear and using the right tools for the job.
7. Test the Repair: Once you've completed the repair, it's important to test it to make sure it's working properly.

8. Keep Records: Keep records of all the repairs and restorations that you perform on your vehicle. This will help you keep track of the vehicle's maintenance history and will come in handy if you ever need to sell it.

With a little know-how and some basic tools, you can easily tackle many common repairs and restorations on your pre-owned vehicle. Just remember to take your time, be careful, and follow the service manual.

只見一群身穿黑白相間作戰服的士兵迅速將測試場團團包圍住，同時測試場內，一架架武裝直升機升空待命，測試場周圍的樹林裏，一群狙擊手潛伏其中，鎖定四周的一切目標。
在測試場中間，一門超大口徑加農炮聳立其中，加農炮炮筒長度足有二十米，直徑足有五米，炮身上還刻着漆黑的“魔王”兩字。
“報告首長，測試場已經佈置完畢，請指示。”一名身穿作戰服的軍官跑到一輛裝甲車前，敬禮報告道。
“很好，開始測試。”裝甲車內，一名身穿黑色軍服的中年男子下令道。
“是！”軍官敬禮，然後轉身下令，“開始測試！”
只聽“轟”的一聲巨響，加農炮炮口噴射出巨大的火舌，將周圍的空氣都燃燒殆盡，一發炮彈拖着長長的尾焰瞬間飛出炮口，直奔測試場遠處的山壁而去。
炮彈擊中山壁，爆發出震耳欲聾的爆炸聲，山壁被炸得粉碎，碎石四濺，硝煙瀰漫。
“報告首長，炮彈命中目標，威力巨大！”軍官激動的彙報道。
“很好，繼續測試。”中年男子滿意的點點頭，下令道。
“是！”軍官敬禮，然後再次下令，“繼續測試！”
隨着軍官的下令，加農炮接連發射出數發炮彈，每一發炮彈都準確的命中目標，將目標炸得粉碎。
測試結束後，中年男子滿意的點點頭，“很好，這次測試非常成功，魔王加農炮的威力超乎我的想象，我相信，有了它，我們千歲烏鴉輕兵器工廠一定會揚名世界！”
“首長，魔王加農炮已經測試成功，下一步我們該怎麼辦？”軍官問道。
“下一步，我們要開始量產魔王加農炮，並將其裝備給我們的部隊，我要讓魔王加農炮成為我們千歲烏鴉輕兵器工廠的王牌武器！”中年男子豪氣干雲的說道。
“是！”軍官激動的敬禮，“首長，我一定會完成任務！”
第二天，千歲烏鴉輕兵器工廠的生產車間裏，無數工人正在加班加點的生產魔王加農炮，生產車間裏熱火朝天，一派繁忙的景象。
時間一天天過去了，魔王加農炮的生產速度越來越快，很快，第一批魔王加農炮便生產出來了。
這些魔王加農炮被運往千歲烏鴉輕兵器工廠的武器庫中，等待着被裝備給部隊。
很快，魔王加農炮便裝備給了千歲烏鴉輕兵器工廠的精銳部隊——魔王軍團。
魔王軍團是一支由千歲烏鴉輕兵器工廠最精鋭的士兵組成的部隊，他們個個身懷絕技，而且裝備精良，其中，魔王加農炮便是他們的王牌武器。
魔王軍團裝備了魔王加農炮後，實力大增，他們在戰場上所向披靡，打敗了一個又一個敵人，讓千歲烏鴉輕兵器工廠的名聲響徹整個黑市世界。
魔王加農炮也因此成為了千歲烏鴉輕兵器工廠的鎮廠之寶，更是被黑市世界譽爲“死神之炮”。",0

163,163,,,"[('', '')]","La nouvelle caméra de surveillance domestique de Google, Nest Cam nouvelle génération, est désormais disponible en France. Commercialisé au prix de 199,99€, cet objet connecté s’appuie sur l’Intelligence Artificielle pour proposer des fonctionnalités supplémentaires, comme la détection intelligente des personnes, animaux et véhicules.
Google Nest Cam : la surveillance domestique intelligente

La Nest Cam nouvelle génération est la nouvelle caméra de surveillance domestique intelligente de Google. Elle succède à la Nest Cam 2020 et apporte de nombreuses améliorations, notamment grâce à l’intégration de la puce Google Tensor.

Cette dernière permet à la caméra de bénéficier de fonctionnalités supplémentaires, comme la détection intelligente des personnes, animaux et véhicules. La Nest Cam nouvelle génération est également capable de suivre les mouvements et de zoomer automatiquement sur les zones d’intérêt.

Outre ses performances en matière d’intelligence artificielle, la Nest Cam nouvelle génération offre également une qualité d’image améliorée. Elle est dotée d’un capteur 12,8 mégapixels et d’un zoom numérique 4K. Elle peut également enregistrer des vidéos en résolution 1080p à 30 images par seconde.

La Nest Cam nouvelle génération est alimentée par une batterie rechargeable et peut être utilisée à l’intérieur comme à l’extérieur. Elle est également compatible avec l’assistant vocal Google Assistant.
La Nest Cam nouvelle génération propose un certain nombre de fonctionnalités, notamment :

* Détection intelligente des personnes, animaux et véhicules : grâce à l’Intelligence Artificielle, la caméra peut détecter les mouvements et les classer en trois catégories : personnes, animaux et véhicules.
* Suivi des mouvements et zoom automatique : la caméra peut suivre les mouvements et zoomer automatiquement sur les zones d’intérêt.
* Qualité d’image améliorée : la Nest Cam nouvelle génération offre une qualité d’image améliorée grâce à son capteur 12,8 mégapixels et à son zoom numérique 4K.
* Enregistrement vidéo en 1080p à 30 images par seconde : la caméra peut enregistrer des vidéos en résolution 1080p à 30 images par seconde.
* Alimentation par batterie rechargeable : la caméra est alimentée par une batterie rechargeable et peut être utilisée à l’intérieur comme à l’extérieur.
* Compatibilité avec l’assistant vocal Google Assistant : la caméra est compatible avec l’assistant vocal Google Assistant et peut être contrôlée à la voix.
La Nest Cam nouvelle génération est disponible en France au prix de 199,99€. Elle peut être achetée sur le site officiel de Google ou auprès de revendeurs agréés.",0

Roksepayer Sürprizleriyle Dolup Taşan DÜNYA ÇOCUK GÜNÜ Festivali

15-17 Kasım tarihleri arasında Rock'n Coke markası ile çocuklara özel düzenlenen DÜNYA ÇOCUK GÜNÜ Festivali, Roksepayer'ların farklı sürprizlerle karşılamalarıyla coşkuya sahne oldu. Mekanın girişinde ""Roksepayerler Kapsamında"" yazılı bir kapı oluşturup, kapıdan çıkan aynı zamanda festivale katılan her ziyaretçilere pipe, balon ve flaşlı tokayla dolu bir ""Roksepayer Paketi"" takdim ettiler. Kalan paketleri de çocuklar için ayrılan köşelerde bulunan çadırlara yerleştirip çocukların istediği kadar almasını, yanında bulundurmasını sağladılar. Bu şekilde Roksepayerlı çocuklar festivalin keyfini daha bir yaşarken, stantları ziyaret ederek bol bol hediye kazandılar, etkinliklerle doyasıya eğlendiler.

Festivalde yeşil ekran önünde uzay kıyafeti ve şapkasıyla boy gösteren Roksepayer, fotoğraf çekilmek isteyenleri profillerinde de kullanabilecekleri hazır bir şablon ile hazır arka planda buluşturuyor, çekimleri direkt olarak mail adreslerine ulaştırıyordu. Roksepayer olmanın en güzel yanlarından biri de bu anlık tezahürattı. Fotoğrafçı ile beraber çocuklara ""Roksepayer"" nidaları attırıp tek karede hepsini çekiyor, fotoğrafları çeken herkese teşekkür ediyor, festivalin doruk noktasındaki anları adeta bir ödüle dönüştürüyordu.

Roksepayer'ın son sürprizi, sahne önlerinde seyirci ile birlikte dans edip festivalin atmosferine kendine has bir canlılık katması oldu. Children of the Sun şarkısı ile rockseverlere selam çakıp, dansı nasıl yaptıklarını, kendine has mimikler ve hareketlerle gösterip hep birlikte coşkuyu ses tellerinden sahneye çağırıyordu.
Roksepayer sürprizlerin devam edeceği bir sonraki festivale kadar bir daha görüşmek ümidiyle seyirciyi selamlayan, festivale damgasını vurdu.",0

Helen Marie Keane, 75 of Strasburg Virginia, passed away peacefully at Johns Hopkins Hospital on December 13, 2022 with her family by her side. Helen was born in Scranton, Pennsylvania to the late James and Rose (Kenney) Moran. She graduated from Scranton Technical High School in 1965. Helen married the love of her life, Patrick Thomas Keane, in 1967. They resided in Scranton, Pennsylvania for 10 years and then moved to Mechanicsburg, Pennsylvania in 1977. They had two children, Patrick Thomas Keane III and Christine Marie Keane. Helen was a homemaker for most of her life but also worked at Giant, The Bon Ton and Mechanicsburg Middle School.

In 2007, Helen and Patrick retired and moved to Strasburg, Virginia to be closer to their daughter and their two precious granddaughters. Helen was a loving and devoted wife, mother, grandmother, sister and aunt. She was a talented seamstress and loved to sew for her family and friends. She also enjoyed cooking, gardening and spending time with her family. Helen was a kind and compassionate person who always put others before herself. She will be deeply missed by all who knew her.
In addition to her parents, she was preceded in death by four brothers, Jack, Tom, Jim and Gerry Moran.
She is survived by her husband of 55 years, Patrick Keane
column2: two children, Patrick T. Keane III (wife Melissa) of Mechanicsburg, Pennsylvania, and Christine Keane of Strasburg, Virginia
column3: two granddaughters, Alexandra Rose Keane and Sophia Marie Keane
column4: a sister, Rosemary Lozier of Scranton, Pennsylvania

column1: A Mass of Christian burial will be held on Friday, December 30, 2022, at 11:00 AM at St. Patrick's Catholic Church in Strasburg, Virginia. Inurnment will follow at St. Patrick's Cemetery.
In lieu of flowers, memorial donations may be made to Johns Hopkins Hospital, 750 E. Pratt St. Suite 1700 Baltimore, MD 21202.
You may sign the guestbook and submit condolences to the family online at www.stoverfuneralhome.com
Stover Funeral Home and Crematory, Strasburg, VA is serving the family of Helen Keane.",0

173,173,,,"[('', '')]","ázatlan viszonyban állhat egymással a két változás, amely elvezetett a Biblia mai formájához. Másfelől a sok különböző információt, amelyet a Biblia tartalmaz, még ha kronológiai sorrendbe és nemzeti egységbe rendezik is, egyetlen könyv keretei között nem lehet mégis minden kronológiai és formális különbség nélkül összehangolni. Mindebből az a következtetés, hogy a Bibliát a közösség megvalósította feladatának tekinti, s nem tekinti úgy, hogy maga a Biblia az a világ, amelyet kifejez. A Bibliának ezt a kettős jellegét a következőkben fogjuk megvizsgálni. A Biblia mint a megvalósított közösség munkája Közösség vs. közösség A Biblia szerves része a zsidóság történetének. Ezért tanulmányozásánál nem szabad elfelejtenünk, hogy létezése nem a zsidóság létezésének oka, hanem éppen fordítva: annak következménye. Azért került sor a különböző bibliai könyvek összeállítására, mert a zsidóság a történelem folyamán különféle módon törekedett arra, hogy közösségi életét megszervezze. A Biblia azonban arra is jó példa, hogy egy közösség mindig arra törekszik, hogy egy olyan világot valósítson meg, amelyet kizárólag saját maga birtokol. Ebből a célból minden mást elutasít, és talán még el is pusztít. Van egy héber szó, amelyet altalában a közösséggel kapcsolatban használnak, és amely magyarázatul szolgál arra vonatkozóan, hogy a Biblia miként kapcsolódik közösségi életéhez. Ez a szó, az edah, ugyanaz, amelyet az egyiptomiak használtak a körök és társaságok kijelölésére. Egy másik szó, a kahal egyenesen arra utal, hogy a közösségnek meghatározott célja van. A zsidóság története folyamán az edah szó a különböző közösségi formákat jelölte: a törzset, a kis közösséget, a várost és a népet mint egészet. A kahal pedig már meghatározott célt tételez föl, és ez a cél a saját egyedülvalóságának megvalósítása. Ahelyett azonban, hogy az igazság, az igazságosság és az egység megvalósítását célzó közösség létrehozásán fáradozna, azon fáradozik, hogy egyedül maradjon. Hogyan érhető ez el? A megfelelő módszer az, hogy kijelenti: a többi közösség vak és süket. Falt emel, amely elválasztja a többi közösségtől, és átkot azokra, akik megpróbálják legyűrni ezt a falat. Az átok élénk részét képezi a mágikus rítusoknak. Bizonyos szekuláris történelemkönyv még az ördög megátkozásáról is beszámol, ami bármennyire is ellentétben van a Biblia hagyományaival, mégis a zsidóság általános véleményét tükrözi. A Biblia azonban nemcsak azt mutatja be, hogyan építette a zsidóság falát a maga körül, hanem azt is, hogyan zajlott az a küzdelem, amelyet a fal lebontására indítottak. A küzdelem több fronton bontakozott ki, de mindenekelőtt ott, ahol a zsidóság hajlamos volt, hogy kizárólag a maga igazát hirdesse. Ez a hajlam nagyban akadályozta a kommunikációt más közösségekkel. A kritikus szemléletű bibliai íróknak sikerült azonban felismerni ezt a hibát. Ők a kommunikációt célul tűzve ki, rögtön felfigyeltek arra, hogy a zsidóság fogságban tartja magát, és ostromot szenved. Ez az ostrom változásokhoz vezet. Először maga a fogság helye merül fel: Babilón, Alexandria, Róma. Majd magának a fogságnak a jellege, amely bizonyos vallási előírások betartására kényszerít, vagy tiltja azok betartását. Végül pedig az, ami minden fogságban a legrosszabb: hogy azt érezzük, egyedül vagyunk. Minden esetben a Biblia összefüggésben áll a zsidóság előtt álló problémák és ezeknek a megoldására irányuló kísérletek különböző formáival. Az egyedülvalóság-probléma megoldására különböző lehetőségek állnak rendelkezésre, amelyeket a Biblia különböző könyveiben találunk meg. Minden probléma egy ideiglenes megoldás lehet, azonban később mindegyiket felváltja egy másfajta problematika. Minden bibliai könyvnek megvan a maga címe, és minden címnek megvan a maga története. A címeknek van egy közös sajátosságuk: megjelölik, hogy mihez kívánnak hozzászólni, és milyen célból. Címek vs. könyvek Minden bibliai könyvnek megvan a maga címe. Minden cím meghatároz bizonyos tartalmat és időbeli keretet. Ez a két tényező együtt kijelöli a könyv műfaját. A megjelölt időbeli keret eltérő lehet. Ha egy bibliai könyv címében szerepel egy helynév (például Babilón vagy Egyiptom), akkor a könyv valószínűleg arról szól, hogy mi történt az adott közösséggel a szóban forgó helyen. Ha egy személynév szerepel a címében (például Mózes vagy Ézsaiás), akkor a könyv valószínűleg az adott személy történetét meséli el. Ha egy intézménynév szerepel a címében, akkor a könyv valószínűleg arról szól, hogy mi történt az adott intézménnyel, és mi lett belőle (például a Törvény, a Templom vagy a Szentély). Ha egy esemény szerepel a címében (például a Kiáltás vagy a Törvény Átadása), akkor a könyv valószínűleg arról szól, hogy mi történt az adott esemény során, és mi lett az esemény következménye. A megjelölt tartalom eltérő lehet. A cím megjelölheti, hogy a könyv milyen műfajú: egy történet, egy dal, egy prófécia vagy egy tanítás, vagy a szerző szándékát, ami lehet: ösztönözni másokat valamilyen cselekvésre, leírni valamilyen eseményt vagy eseménysorozatot, tanítani valamit vagy elmesélni egy történetet. A cím használata azonban még korántsem olyan egyszerű, mint ahogy ez első pillantásra tűnik. Minden cím egy olyan homályos jelzés, amelyet sokféleképpen lehet értelmezni. Ennek az a következménye, hogy minden könyvnek több címe van, és mindegyik cím más kontextusba helyezi a könyvet. Például az Exodus szónak két jelentése van: kijutás és kiáltozás. Ebből a két jelentésből különböző könyvek születtek, amelyek mindegyike a maga módján foglalkozik a kiáltással és a kijutással. A kiáltással foglalkozó könyv az Exodus könyve, a kijutással pedig a Mózes könyve. Az Exodus szó két különböző jelentését más módon is meg lehet különböztetni egymástól. Ha a cím hármas határozott névelőt használ (hat-torah, hat-debarim, hat-tora), akkor egy pontos, jól körülhatárolt, komplex és így szigorúan formális könyvvel van dolgunk. Ha a cím nem használ hármas határozott névelőt (torah, debarim, tora), akkor egy olyan könyvvel van dolgunk, amely többek között tartalmaz történeteket, mondásokat és szimbolikus cselekedeteket. A cím alapján nem mindig tudjuk megmondani, hogy mi a könyv műfaja és tartalma. A könyv maga dönti el, hogy hogyan használja fel a címet, amelyet hozzárendeltek. A cím ház, a könyv pedig a ház belseje, amelyet a ház lakói szerveznek meg. A cím és a könyv közötti különbség több okból is fontos. Először is, a címet a közösség hagyományozza. Minden könyvnek megvan a maga címe, de a címet nem mindig a könyv írója találta ki. A cím valószínűleg a hagyomány által adományoztatott a könyvre. A hagyomány kényszerítheti a szerzőt arra, hogy a címnek megfelelő tartalmú könyvet írjon. Másodszor, a címet a közösség használ",0

Saara Johanna Turunen (n. el 2 de septiembre de 1981) fue una cantante finlandesa. Ella fue la vocalista de la banda finesa de heavy/power metal Tarot hasta que fue sustituida por Marco Hietala. Ella es también la hermana de la cantante Tarja Turunen, exintegrante de Nightwish. Actualmente es la cantante de la banda Finnish metal band Outloud y que además lanzó en el año 2007 un EP en solitario llamado ´´Outcast´´.
Saara nació en Kitee, Finlandia y comenzó a cantar a la edad de 7 años. A los 20 años, se trasladó a Alemania para unirse a Tarot.
Saara se unió a la banda en 2003 y grabó el álbum For the Glory of Nothing. En 2005, la banda lanzó el álbum Suffer Our Pleasures, pero Saara decidió dejar la banda.
En 2007, Saara lanzó su primer EP en solitario, llamado Outcast. El EP fue producido por Matias Kupiainen, guitarrista de Stratovarius.
En 2010, Saara se unió a la banda Outloud con la que ha grabado dos álbumes
* 2003 - Tarot - For The Glory of Nothing (con Tarot)
Is it impermissible to make dua’ (supplication) to Allah (ﷻ) after the sun has set on Friday night?

It has been narrated in Sahih al-Bukhari, Sahih Muslim and other major texts of Hadith that the Prophet (ﷺ) said: “There is an hour on Friday, whereon a Muslim who makes dua’ to Allah (ﷻ), it will certainly be accepted.”

There are differences of opinion amongst the scholars as to when this one hour exactly is. Some imams said it is at the time of Asr prayer. Others said it is after Asr prayer until sunset. This opinion is attributed to the majority of imams, including Imam Malik (may Allah have mercy on him).
Ibn Qudamah (may Allah have mercy on him) said in al-Mughni (2/375), “The scholars agree that the sun setting constitutes the end of the day, which includes Friday night.”

Therefore, it is permissible to make dua’ to Allah (ﷻ) and ask Him for anything you wish at any time on Friday, so long as the sun is not set. Once Friday night commences with the sunset, it is no longer possible to catch that particular accepted hour.",0

178,178,,,"[('', '')]","Volkswagen has announced several changes to its top-level management following the recent emissions scandal, including the resignation of CEO Martin Winterkorn.

The most significant change is the appointment of Matthias Müller as the new CEO. Müller is currently the CEO of Porsche, a subsidiary of Volkswagen. He has been with the Volkswagen Group for over 20 years and is seen as a safe pair of hands to lead the company through this difficult time.

Other changes include the resignation of Wolfgang Porsche and Ferdinand Piëch from the Volkswagen Group’s Supervisory Board. Porsche and Piëch are both members of the Porsche and Piëch families, which own a majority stake in Volkswagen.
Hans Dieter Pötsch, the current CFO of Volkswagen, will become the new Chairman of the Supervisory Board. Pötsch is a highly experienced executive who has been with Volkswagen for over 30 years.

These changes are a clear attempt by Volkswagen to draw a line under the emissions scandal and start afresh. The company is facing huge fines and legal challenges, and it needs to rebuild its reputation.

Müller is a respected and experienced executive who is seen as capable of leading Volkswagen through this crisis. He has a strong track record at Porsche, and he is known for his decisiveness and his ability to get things done.

The changes to the Supervisory Board are also significant. Porsche and Piëch have been powerful figures at Volkswagen for many years, and their departure marks the end of an era. Pötsch is a more independent figure, and he is likely to bring a fresh perspective to the company.

These changes at the top of Volkswagen are a sign that the company is serious about changing its ways. The emissions scandal has been a huge blow to the company’s reputation, and it is clear that Volkswagen needs to take drastic action to rebuild its credibility.",0

180,180,,,"[('', '')]","Active Citizenship: A New Model of Development? About the author Marjorie Taylor Marjorie Taylor is an anthropologist, researcher and consultant with more than 30 years of experience in international development. She has worked throughout Africa, the Middle East, Latin America and Asia for non-governmental organizations, the United Nations, and the British and Canadian governments. Her interest in active citizenship has grown out of serving as a consultant to the Active Citizens Programme of the British Council. For many, the words ""active citizenship"" are interchangeable with ""good citizenship"" or ""civic responsibility."" Active citizenship is often used by government to emphasize the importance of citizens paying their taxes, obeying the law and participating in community service. Governments sometimes use the term in contrast to the concept of citizenship rights. Rather than defining active citizens as people who can access essential public services, they talk about active citizens as those who should police their communities or pay higher taxes. However, the concept of active citizenship encompasses much more than these limited definitions suggest. As defined by the Active Citizenship Network, the European network of foundations, activists and researchers active in promoting democratic participation, active citizenship includes the following three key elements: Individuals identifying themselves as citizens
column2: Individuals acting to influence their communities, societies and governments
column3: and Individuals working for the common good. Active citizenship is about citizens developing their potential, making choices and contributing to society in all aspects of their lives rather than just through political or community engagement. Importantly, active citizenship is a matter of attitudes and values as much as it is about activities or behaviours. It involves the development of competencies and a sense of self-confidence and self-esteem. People believe they can make a difference, are able to identify what is in their common interest, and are prepared to take action to effect change. As a result, active citizens are more likely to be engaged in influencing the decisions that affect their lives and their communities. This concept of active citizenship is an emerging one. While the phrase itself has been in use for a number of years, it is only recently that the concept has begun to be used by researchers, policymakers and practitioners to help explain and understand the ways in which people exercise their citizenship in modern democracies. While it is still not universally or precisely defined, active citizenship is increasingly recognized for its potential contribution to more democratic, just and prosperous societies. Theories and models of active citizenship Most theories and models of active citizenship locate it within the broader framework of social and political theory, especially democratic theory. They emphasize how people can exercise their citizenship rights and responsibilities effectively and how citizens can engage with government and community in meaningful ways. Scholars have identified a variety of factors that influence whether or not people are active citizens, as well as the forms of activism in which they engage. Such factors include: Personal circumstances (such as age, education, ethnicity, gender, income and social background)
column4: The level of trust that people have in government, political institutions and others in their communities
column5: The extent to which people have access to resources and opportunities
column6: and The role of civil society organizations in intermediary and bridging roles between citizens, communities and government. Active citizenship in development The idea of active citizenship is increasingly being promoted by governments and development agencies as a way to engage people in development processes and to improve local governance and service delivery. However, the application of this concept in development interventions and programming has not kept pace with its growing appeal. Too often, active citizenship is limited to the narrow concept of civic education or community mobilization for the implementation of specific projects. The reasons for this are complex, but they include: The short-term orientation and instrumental approach to development that often fails to recognize the importance of the attitudes and behaviours that underpin active citizenship
column7: The focus on measurable results that undervalues the importance of the long-term capacity building necessary to support active citizenship
column8: The lack of specialized knowledge and skills among development practitioners to incorporate active citizenship into their work, as well as a lack of relevant training opportunities
column9: and The difficulties encountered by development agencies in providing adequate support to the community-based organizations that are key partners in promoting active citizenship. Despite these challenges, the promotion of active citizenship has been a central feature of a number of innovative development initiatives. Perhaps the most cited examples are participatory projects and programmes in which people's involvement is key to the planning, implementation and monitoring of development interventions. The experiences of these initiatives provide some important insights into how the concept of active citizenship might be used more effectively to bridge the gap between people and their institutions and to encourage more sustainable and equitable development outcomes. Participatory projects underscore the importance of the following four principles: People's engagement in decision-making processes
column10: Collective action for the common good
column11: Long-term commitment to nurturing local ownership of initiatives
column12: and Building on existing capacities and resources. These principles reflect the key elements of active citizenship and are fundamental to the promotion of sustainable development. When these principles are applied, people who have previously been excluded from decision-making processes are more likely to participate in and benefit from development interventions. Furthermore, when people are involved in decision-making, they are more likely to feel a sense of ownership over the decisions that affect their lives and to support the implementation of decisions. This, in turn, leads to improved performance and accountability. Participatory projects can also strengthen relationships between people and public authorities, and provide a platform for dialogue and negotiation that can improve public policymaking and service delivery. Active citizenship in a global context Active citizenship is not confined to particular cultures, contexts or countries, but is a characteristic of all citizens. However, the particular forms of active citizenship and the ways in which it is exercised vary across different societies. This is because the exercise of citizenship is shaped by a wide range of social, economic, cultural and political factors, including the history of the country, its social institutions, its level of economic development and its political system. These factors help to explain why the role of non-governmental organizations (NGOs) in promoting active citizenship is particularly significant in many parts of the world. In some countries, independent NGOs are one of the few opportunities available for people to participate outside traditional structures and are highly valued as a means of expressing citizenship rights. In other countries, NGOs are seen as a potential threat to government authority and are subject to strict regulations that limit their ability to function effectively. Even when NGOs have relative freedom to operate, their efforts to promote active citizenship can be restricted by other factors, such as legal barriers (e.g., laws against public assembly), cultural norms (e.g., gender roles that limit women's participation in public life), economic inequalities (e.g., lack of access to education and discrimination against certain ethnic groups), or security risks (e.g., in conflict-affected countries). While these factors pose a number of challenges to those promoting active citizenship, they also point to the importance of recognizing the different ways in which citizens across the world exercise their citizenship rights and responsibilities and the need to be flexible and adaptive in approaching development. Active citizenship as a new model of development? The concept of active citizenship is gaining traction among development thinkers and practitioners. Many see it as a new model of development that can help to address a number of the problems associated with the traditional top-down approach. The promotion of active citizenship has the potential to: Strengthen relations between people and their institutions, thus improving governance and accountability
column13: Create more opportunities for people to participate in decision-making processes that affect their lives
column14: Build social capital and empower marginalized groups
column15: and Empower people to hold government and other agencies accountable, leading to improved public service delivery. If properly implemented, active citizenship strategies can lead to a new model of development based on principles of inclusion, equity and sustainability. However, there are also risks associated with the promotion of active citizenship. In certain circumstances, active citizenship could be used to mobilize people in support of oppressive regimes or could lead to the exclusion of marginalized groups. The risk of abuse of the concept of active citizenship can be reduced through attention to the following issues: Who is promoting active citizenship and for what purpose? Are the processes participatory, transparent, inclusive and accountable? Does the approach support people's ability to exercise their citizenship rights and contribute effectively to the development of their communities? As the concept of active citizenship continues to evolve and practitioners and policymakers pay more attention to promoting active citizenship, it will be important to monitor its impact and refine the approach to ensure that it is making a positive contribution to development. Notes 1 A New Model of Active Citizenship: Increasing Participation, Improving Governance, Creating Sustainability, which was a paper prepared by the Active Citizenship Network in partnership with the think tank Demos, in preparation for the European Year of Active Citizenship 2013. 2 Ibid. 3 Active citizenship was defined in a Manifesto for Active Citizenship adopted by the Foundation for the Future and published in the New Economics magazine, Vol. 4, No. 1 (2007). 4 These key elements were identified in a document entitled Key Components of Active Citizenship: An Active Citizenship Network Working Paper, October 2010. 5 The Active Citizenship Network is an initiative of the European Foundation Centre and CIVICUS: World Alliance for Citizen Participation. 6 Ibid. 7 Robert Putnam, Bowling Alone: The Collapse and Revival of American Community (New York: Simon and Schuster, 2000). 8 See the work of the Australian Centre for Corporate Social Responsibility, formerly the Centre for Corporate Citizenship. 9 Ibid. 10 For example, the active citizenship framework developed by the Active Learning Network for Accountability and Performance in Humanitarian Action (ALNAP) to guide humanitarian advocacy. 11 See, for example, Campaigns for Social Justice by Citizen-Led Movements, IDS Practice Paper No. 8, July 2009, authored by Kevin Watkins, and one of a series of studies produced by the Institute of Development Studies. 12 For example, the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) has been actively promoting active citizenship as a dimension of human development. 13 For example, the Active Citizens Programme of the British Council has been implemented in over 50 countries since its inception in 2",0
